On Wed, 31 Oct 2001, doc ric wrote:

> The guy at the FLAPS suggests a HD clutch disc. Same size, heavier springs.
> Is made for some diesel application. What do you think? (He also wanted me
> to use a modified cam but I declined). :-)

If the stock disk isn't slipping, there is no reason to go to a heavy duty
disk.  Doing so will only put more load on the clutch cable and associated
components, as well as your foot.

